Interactive Quiz App
Description
The Interactive Quiz App is a dynamic web-based application that allows users to test their knowledge through a series of multiple-choice questions. The app highlights correct answers, tracks the score, and provides feedback at the end of the quiz. It is built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript/jQuery.

Features
Dynamically loads quiz questions and answer options.
Highlights the correct answer and shows feedback after each question.
Keeps track of the user's score.
Fully responsive design with a modern, attractive UI.
Easy navigation through questions with a "Next" button.
Project Structure
bash
Copy
Edit
Interactive Quiz App/
│
├── index.html          # Main HTML file for the quiz app
├── css/
│   └── style.css       # Styling for the quiz app
├── js/
│   └── script.js       # Logic and functionality of the quiz app
└── README.md           # Project documentation
Technologies Used
HTML5: Structure of the web application.
CSS3: Styling and animations for an enhanced user experience.
JavaScript: Application logic, including dynamic question handling.
jQuery: DOM manipulation and event handling.
Getting Started
Prerequisites
To run this project, you only need a web browser that supports JavaScript.

Setup
Clone the repository:
bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/your-username/interactive-quiz-app.git
Navigate to the project folder:
bash
Copy
Edit
cd interactive-quiz-app
Open index.html in your web browser:
bash
Copy
Edit
open index.html
Usage
The app will load the first question when opened.
Select an option to see if your answer is correct or wrong.
Click the Next button to navigate to the next question.
At the end of the quiz, your score will be displayed.
